The following class includes two null check conditionals. Both conditionals are tautologies, because `Class.getName()` never returns `null`. IntelliJ's nullability analysis detects that the first conditional is a tautology, but it reports that the second conditional is always false. The second conditional class `Class.getName()` with a local class.

```java
public class T {

  void expected() {
    if (T.class.getName() == null) {
      System.out.println("This can never happen");
    }
  }

  void unexpected() {
    class F { }
    if (F.class.getName() == null) {
      System.out.println("This can never happen");
    }
  }
}
```

